### ============================================
### FastAPI Backend API Tests
### ============================================
### Base URL: http://localhost:8000
### Start the server with: python run.py
### ============================================

### Health Check
GET http://localhost:8000/api/health

### ============================================
### SSE (Server-Sent Events) Endpoints
### ============================================

### SSE Health Check
GET http://localhost:8000/api/sse/health

### SSE Connection (Server-Sent Events)
# This will keep the connection open and stream events
GET http://localhost:8000/api/sse

### Publish Navigation Event
POST http://localhost:8000/api/navigation
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "event": "navigation",
  "data": {
    "page": "dashboard",
    "userId": "test-user-123",
    "timestamp": "2026-02-25T18:00:00Z"
  }
}

### ============================================
### Available Services
### ============================================

### Get All Available Services
GET http://localhost:8000/api/available-services

### ============================================
### Case Management APIs
### ============================================

### Get Case Details by ID
GET http://localhost:8000/api/case/1

### Get Documents for a Case
GET http://localhost:8000/api/case/1/documents

### Get Extracted Key Metrics for a Case
GET http://localhost:8000/api/case/1/extracted-key-metrics

### Get Covenant Status for a Case
GET http://localhost:8000/api/case/1/covenant-status

### Get Quarterly DSCR for a Case
GET http://localhost:8000/api/case/1/quarterly-dscr

### Get Quarter-by-Quarter Financial Drivers for a Case
GET http://localhost:8000/api/case/1/quarter-by-quarter-financial-drivers

### Get Q3 Highlights for a Case
GET http://localhost:8000/api/case/1/q3-highlights

### Get FR Y14 Schedule Template Data for a Case
GET http://localhost:8000/api/case/1/fr-y14-schedule-template

### Get Y14 Detailed Findings for a Case
GET http://localhost:8000/api/case/1/y14-detailed-findings

### Get Shipment Details for a Case
GET http://localhost:8000/api/case/1/shipment-details

### Get Operational Findings for a Case
GET http://localhost:8000/api/case/1/operational-doc-scan-detailed-findings

### Get Data Simulator Benefits for a Case
GET http://localhost:8000/api/case/1/data-simulator-benefits

### ============================================
### Test with Different Case IDs
### ============================================

### Test with non-existent case (should return 404)
GET http://localhost:8000/api/case/999999

### Test with string case ID (should handle gracefully)
GET http://localhost:8000/api/case/test-case-id

### ============================================
### Error Handling Tests
### ============================================

### Test invalid endpoint (should return 404)
GET http://localhost:8000/api/nonexistent-endpoint

### Test invalid method on existing endpoint (should return 405)
POST http://localhost:8000/api/health

### Test malformed JSON (should return 422)
POST http://localhost:8000/api/navigation
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "event": "navigation",
  "data": {
    "page": "dashboard"
    // Missing closing brace - malformed JSON
  }

### ============================================
### CORS Headers Test
### ============================================

### Test with Origin header to verify CORS
GET http://localhost:8000/api/health
Origin: http://localhost:3000

### ============================================
### Performance Tests
### ============================================

### Multiple concurrent requests (copy-paste multiple times)
GET http://localhost:8000/api/health
GET http://localhost:8000/api/health
GET http://localhost:8000/api/health

### ============================================
### API Documentation
### ============================================

### Interactive API Docs (Swagger UI)
# Open in browser: http://localhost:8000/docs

### ReDoc Documentation
# Open in browser: http://localhost:8000/redoc

### OpenAPI Schema
GET http://localhost:8000/openapi.json

### ============================================
### Notes:
### ============================================
### 1. Make sure the server is running before executing these requests
### 2. For SSE endpoint, the connection will stay open - you'll see real-time events
### 3. Case IDs used in examples (123) may not exist - expect empty results or 404s
### 4. To test with real data, first insert some test records into the database
### 5. Use VS Code REST Client extension or similar to execute these requests
### 6. For POST requests with navigation events, you can modify the data payload as needed
